I. Overview:
This week, the primary focus was on understanding the Smart City Traffic Forecasting
problem and working with time series data using Python. Efforts were made to explore
the dataset, perform preprocessing, and begin initial analysis of traffic patterns across
different junctions. Additionally, learning resources were utilized to strengthen
knowledge in data analysis and forecasting techniques.
II. Achievements:
1. Project Familiarization:
Understood the problem statement of forecasting traffic patterns for smart city
development.
Explored the dataset structure, including features such as DateTime, Junction, and
Vehicles.
Identified the importance of traffic variation based on time, weekdays, and special events.
2. Python Project Contributions:
Name of the project: Forecasting of Smart City Traffic Patterns
Loaded and processed both training and testing datasets using Python.
Performed data cleaning, including handling missing values and formatting DateTime.
Implemented feature engineering by extracting hour, day, month, and weekday.
Conducted basic exploratory data analysis to visualize traffic trends.
3. Learning Python:
Gained hands-on experience with Python libraries such as Pandas, NumPy, Matplotlib,
and Seaborn.
Learned time series data handling and preprocessing techniques.
Applied Python skills to analyze real-world traffic data
